   Hello everybody out there in the MAXs scene! ..Here's another silly
   doc of mine, for those who enjoy reading 'em! :) [ Version 1.1 ]

   Yes, it's yet @{b}another@{ub} MAXs door/product by me, Glen Martin! :) I've
   lost count of how many  MAXs doors and support files I've done now,
   whether they be good or bad?! Well, I enjoy doing it as it's one of
   my hobbies, and will continue writting doors,  as long as I have my
   great GREMLiNS BBS online (2 yrs now),  so I'm supportive, and show
   me your @{" support " link call} by emailing me, or calling the BBS?! ..It's CooL!

   Anyways, enuff krap.. wat's "Speed", u all ask... No, not a drug, &
   not an excuse to drive like sum of the Fluffy SysOps ....but a door
   that allows the users (and SysOp) to skip the doors that would have
   been, or are executed via the "Introdoor.text" process (it can also
   skip thru' the Maindoor.text, too). Hmmmm, that's not new.. I know,
   but it had to be done! :) So in brief, wen it's run, it prompts the
   user to whether they want to skip the "Introdoor.text" doors and go
   straight to (skip to) the "new msg check" prompt. That's it, easy!!

   Just @{" install " link run} and run the door and see for yaself! ..Wow, no shit!


