@node run " Speed - by Glen Martin of GREMLiNS BBS"
 @{"°°" link grems}
     ___ ___ ___ ___ ____
    / __| _ \ __| __|  _ \  @{"°"} @{" Install "} @{"°°"} @{"°"}
    \__ \  _/ _|| _|| |_) |
    |___/_| |___|___|____/  @{b}(c) 1998 GREMLiNS MAXsWARE plus NSA & LSD@{ub}


   For those who read and love my docs, u know wat I usually say... If
   ya can't work it out for yaself, your a braindead SysOp! ;)

   Anyways, u unpack the archive (already done obviously smart-arse) &
   then u create a "new directory" called "gremlins" in your doors dir
   wich is easy.  I've decided and to meet requests from sum SysOps, I
   am now placing all my doors (old updates and new) into a "main" dir
   called "gremlins" so to keep it all tidy, etc and keep all my doors
   together, for some reason.. Okay!? Stiff shit if not & piss off! ;)

   Okie dokie, follow these simple (?) steps:

   o You  must put an  "assign" command in  your startup  sequence and
     this is, eg: assign gremlins: bbs:doors/gremlins .

   o Move the "speed dir" and files inside into the "gremlins dir" and
     run it from there via MAXs, eg: gremlins:speed/speed .

   o Then  edit your "Introdoor.text" to run your intro doors from the
     "Speed dir"  such  as, eg: gremlins:speed/<doorname>. See example
     included in archive. Each of the doors (<doorname>, the exe only)
     run during intro login must be copied to the "Speed dir" as well.
     Why?  Wen a user logs in,  the BBS  executes the "Introdoor.text"
     doors in  "gremlins:speed/" path, and if the user doesn't want  a
     speedy login,  the doors run as normal,  and if they do,  "Speed"
     renames the "Speed dir" to "Speedy",  and thus the BBS can't find
     the door paths,  eg: gremlins/speed/<doorname> as the "Speed dir"
     don't exist, and doesn't run the doors & skips  thru to "new msgs
     check"! Understand? To rename it back after "Speed" is done, have
     the following line,  eg: gremlins:speedy/speedy as  the last door
     command in "Introdoor.text", again, see the example included.

   o When door is run, "Speed.menu" is  shown, and if [i]nfo  selected
     will show "Speed.nfo". You may alter these screens, but...

   You, hopefully, should get it working and know wat to do from here.
   Any probs, u know who to @{" contact " link call}, cool?! ;)


